  "prompt": "What are some karaoke songs for a 2nd alto?",
  "response": "Here are some great karaoke songs that suit a second alto vocal range, which typically sits comfortably in the lower mezzo-soprano or alto range (around G3 to E5). These songs allow for rich, warm tones and avoid excessively high notes:\n\n### Pop/R&B:\n1. **Adele** - \"Rolling in the Deep\"  \n2. **Amy Winehouse** - \"Valerie\"  \n3. **Sia** - \"Chandelier\" (lower key)  \n4. **H.E.R.** - \"Best Part\" (feat. Daniel Caesar)  \n5. **Lorde** - \"Royals\"  \n\n### Rock:\n6. **Bon Jovi** - \"Livin' on a Prayer\"  \n7. **Fleetwood Mac** - \"Landslide\" (sung by Stevie Nicks)  \n8. **Alanis Morissette** - \"You Oughta Know\"  \n9. **P!nk** - \"So What\"  \n10. **Heart** - \"Barracuda\"  \n\n### Country:\n11. **Shania Twain** - \"Man! I Feel Like a Woman!\"  \n12. **Kacey Musgraves** - \"Follow Your Arrow\"  \n13. **Dolly Parton** - \"Jolene\"  \n14. **Miranda Lambert** - \"The House That Built Me\"  \n15. **Maren Morris** - \"My Church\"  \n\n### Jazz/Blues:\n16. **Etta James** - \"At Last\"  \n17. **Billie Holiday** - \"God Bless the Child\"  \n18. **Norah Jones** - \"Don\u2019t Know Why\"  \n19. **Dinah Washington** - \"What a Diff\u2019rence a Day Made\"  \n20. **Ella Fitzgerald** - \"Summertime\"  \n\n### Musical Theater/Disney:\n21. **\"Defying Gravity\"** (from *Wicked*) (lower key)  \n22. **\"When He Sees Me\"** (from *Waitress*)  \n23. **\"Part of Your World\"** (from *The Little Mermaid*)  \n24. **\"I Dreamed a Dream\"** (from *Les Mis\u00e9rables*)  \n25. **\"Journey to the Past\"** (from *Anastasia*)  \n\n### Classic Hits:\n26. **Tina Turner** - \"What\u2019s Love Got to Do with It\"  \n27. **Blondie** - \"One Way or Another\"  \n28. **Cyndi Lauper** - \"Time After Time\"  \n29. **The Pretenders** - \"Brass in Pocket\"  \n30. **Stevie Nicks** - \"Edge of Seventeen\"  \n\nWhen choosing a song, consider keys and vocal arrangements. Many of these songs can be transposed to better suit your range if needed. Have fun singing! \ud83c\udfa4",
